http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Pongal-book-fair-to-go-on-till-tomorrow/article14019387.ece

Crowds continued to visit the Chennai Pongal Book festival at YMCA Grounds in Royapettah on Sunday and as organisers announced that event will be extended for two more days, the joy of book lovers knew no bounds.Among the visitors to the festival, K. Sudhakar of Padur said he had been motivating people living in his village and the surrounding areas to visit the book festival.“We were able to arrange buses on weekends and during Pongal to help people attend the festival. Many people, who live far away from the city, are either unaware of this event or find it difficult to get here,” he said.Rising interestMore than 70 people from the area visited the book fair on Sunday. “There is now a definite increase in interest in reading among youngsters and we are happy about this. Educational institutions from Nagapattinam and Kumbakonam are among those who visited the fair to buy books for their libraries,” said K. Nagarajan from Bharathi Publishers.On Sunday, ten authors were honoured for their contribution to Tamil literature: S. Madasamy, Manushyaputhiran, Eknath, S. Arshiya, Bhagiyam Shankar, P.N.S. Pandian, S. Devadas, Satheesh Muthu, Priya Thambi and Pavanan.R.S. Shanmugham, trustee of Tamil Nadu Book Sales and Promotions Association, said they had recorded a footfall of nearly 2 lakh.“Tamil books, which detail history and heritage as well as biographies of public figures, are popular among youth as well as families. Children’s books in both Tamil and English are popular too,” he said.